1
00:00:00,125 --> 00:00:04,625
Sometimes it came in a pot, and sometimes in a bowl, depending on the meal

2
00:00:04,750 --> 00:00:10,208
There was no special food, the food was served to everyone, they did not have specific food for anyone

3
00:00:10,791 --> 00:00:11,833
Interviewer: What kind of food?

4
00:00:11,958 --> 00:00:16,791
Rice, and sometimes in the morning yogurt, and things like that

5
00:00:16,833 --> 00:00:17,958
Interviewer: What was for breakfast?

6
00:00:18,166 --> 00:00:19,666
Yogurt and the like, and bread

7
00:00:20,041 --> 00:00:22,250
Interviewer: What was given to each person or prisoner?

8
00:00:22,333 --> 00:00:24,458
There was no portion for each person, at noon they brought a big platter of rice and meat

9
00:00:25,291 --> 00:00:28,916
Or they brought a pot of food, and everyone ate together

10
00:00:29,375 --> 00:00:30,375
Everyone was the same

11
00:00:30,666 --> 00:00:32,958
Whether you were full, ate, or did not eat

12
00:00:33,166 --> 00:00:36,083
You could not tell him you were hungry, and you could not say, Bring me more food

13
00:00:36,791 --> 00:00:40,625
Interviewer: For example, in the morning did each person have a specific <i>samoon</i> [bread roll]?

14
00:00:40,708 --> 00:00:44,208
No, a bag of <i>samoon</i> would come and everyone sat to eat

15
00:00:44,750 --> 00:00:47,041
Interviewer: How much was your share of <i>samoon</i>, one piece or two?

16
00:00:47,333 --> 00:00:51,666
Some ate three pieces of <i>samoon</i>, some two, and some did not eat out of distress

17
00:00:52,333 --> 00:00:53,625
Interviewer: Was the <i>samoon</i> enough?

18
00:00:54,083 --> 00:00:55,375
Interviewer: Did any <i>samoon</i> remain?

19
00:00:55,458 --> 00:00:57,666
No, none of it was left

20
00:00:59,250 --> 00:01:02,875
Interviewer: In your view, was this food cooked inside this building or did it come from outside?

21
00:01:03,125 --> 00:01:04,833
No, it likely came from outside this building

22
00:01:05,750 --> 00:01:09,458
That is obvious, if it was cooked in this building there would have been a smell of food

23
00:01:09,875 --> 00:01:12,041
It could have been cooked here and we did not know

24
00:01:12,666 --> 00:01:15,458
Because you were in a room and did not know your fate

25
00:01:16,416 --> 00:01:22,250
Because of fear and anxiety, nothing stayed in your head

26
00:01:22,541 --> 00:01:25,125
Interviewer: Was there any change in the food? For example, today rice

27
00:01:25,208 --> 00:01:28,041
Tomorrow bulgur and then chickpeas? Or was it all rice?

28
00:01:28,208 --> 00:01:30,375
No, just rice and beans, and things like that

29
00:01:31,708 --> 00:01:34,125
Interviewer: Was it the same type of food the whole time? Witness: Yes

30
00:01:34,416 --> 00:01:38,666
There was, for example, a time when they had a feast

31
00:01:38,958 --> 00:01:40,500
They would give us whatever was left over from it

32
00:01:41,416 --> 00:01:43,666
They gave their leftovers to the prisoners

33
00:01:44,375 --> 00:01:47,666
Interviewer: Was the rice mixed with the broth, or separate?

34
00:01:47,833 --> 00:01:49,125
No, it was separate

35
00:01:49,791 --> 00:01:52,333
Interviewer: The containers they served in, were they plastic?

36
00:01:52,416 --> 00:01:54,000
Made of plastic, plastic

37
00:01:54,333 --> 00:01:57,166
Interviewer: Did you have tea?

38
00:01:57,416 --> 00:01:59,625
Tea was scarce, it was served only in the morning

39
00:02:00,958 --> 00:02:03,041
Interviewer: Did they serve you tea?
Witness: Only in the morning

40
00:02:04,041 --> 00:02:05,416
Interviewer: A cup for each person?

41
00:02:05,500 --> 00:02:10,083
No, no, it came in a thermos

42
00:02:11,250 --> 00:02:14,208
It was enough if each person drank one cup

43
00:02:15,041 --> 00:02:18,250
Interviewer: Were the cups plastic?
Witness: Yes, plastic

44
00:02:18,958 --> 00:02:20,416
Interviewer: When they brought in the food

45
00:02:20,833 --> 00:02:23,083
Did the jailer open the door and bring in the food?

46
00:02:23,250 --> 00:02:28,375
Or would he open the door and call one of you that the food was outside, come take it?

47
00:02:29,041 --> 00:02:33,916
As soon as he brought the food, he would hand it through the door and anyone would take it from him

48
00:02:34,458 --> 00:02:35,458
And he would leave and close the door

49
00:02:36,083 --> 00:02:39,666
Before he served the food, you had finished the previous meal and collected it in a bag

50
00:02:39,750 --> 00:02:41,250
He would take the bag and give you the second meal

51
00:02:41,833 --> 00:02:44,416
Interviewer: Did you have water available, drinking water?

52
00:02:44,500 --> 00:02:49,291
Water was available, drinking water, and if it was cut off there was water from the tank

53
00:02:49,750 --> 00:02:53,458
Interviewer: Did each person have a specific share, or could you ask at any time?

54
00:02:54,291 --> 00:02:55,916
No, there was no specific share

55
00:02:56,250 --> 00:02:58,833
They brought water for drinking, and there would be some left
